<spirit:busDefinition xmlns:spirit="http://www.spiritconsortium.org/XMLSchema/SPIRIT/1685-2009" xmlns:arm="http://www.arm.com/SPIRIT/1685-2009" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.spiritconsortium.org/XMLSchema/SPIRIT/1685-2009 http://www.spiritconsortium.org/XMLSchema/SPIRIT/1685-2009/index.xsd">
    <spirit:vendor>amba.com</spirit:vendor>
    <spirit:library>AMBA4</spirit:library>
    <spirit:name>P-Channel</spirit:name>
    <spirit:version>r0p0_0</spirit:version>
    <spirit:directConnection>true</spirit:directConnection>
    <spirit:isAddressable>false</spirit:isAddressable>
    <spirit:description>The purpose of this interface is to prepare a device for certain power states.
There are 2 signal groups:
  activity indicators (PACTIVE[N-1:0]), and
  the handshake signal group (PSTATE[M-1:0], PREQ, PACCEPT, and PDENY.
PACTIVE[N-1:0] may be sparse or omitted.  PDENY is optional.
For more information please refer to the AMBA Low Power Interface Specification ARM IHI 0068D : http://www.arm.com/support/AMBA.html</spirit:description>
